cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses secure compilers and their ability to withstand attacks, making it highly relevant to the cryptography and security sub-category.
2. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses compilers and their ability to preserve safety properties of the source program, making it relevant to the programming languages sub-category.
3. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses techniques for developing secure and efficient compilers, which is relevant to the software engineering sub-category.
4. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper discusses proof techniques for establishing that a compiler attains RSC, which is relevant to the logic in computer science sub-category.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the efficiency of compiled code, which is relevant to the systems and control sub-category.
